	<h3>Various varieties of Pangas fish</h3>
	<p>Among the species of Pangas, native Pangas and Thai Pangas are the most popular. Let's now know some information about their identity,
	<br>
<h5>Domestic Pangas:</h5> The country's pangas are dark brown in the back of the silver-colored backs and on the side line. There is no fiber in this fish. Still, our native species of Pangas is delicious and at a higher price. This fish is found in Padma, Meghna, Bahmiputra and Jamuna rivers of Bangladesh. They may survive in adverse environments. For the months of March to June, its fona is found in the main rivers, including the various rivers of the southern region of the country.
<br>
<h5>Thai Pangas: </h5>Adivas in Thailand, in the countries of Compuchia, Vietnam and neighboring regions. In the first place in our country, it was possible to successfully breed fishes in foreign countries in 1993. Today, Thai Pangas is a popular name for commercial cultivation. This species has increased rapidly than the native Pangas. This fish is up to 10-12 kg.</p>
		<h3>Pangas fish farming method</h3>
		
		<p>The method of fish farming depends on the characteristics of ponds or water bodies, environmental conditions, water control management, capital, quality fodder and market management. Keeping these factors in mind, it is important to decide how the cultivation process will be. Today we will know about single farming of pangas or intensive cultivation.
        </p>
		<h3>Pond selection:</h3>
		<p>
		<ul><li>It is good to rectangle the pond farming pond. The floor of the pond should be well flattened. The depth of the pond should be kept from 1.5 to 2 meters.</li>
         <li>Looping soil pond is best for pigeon cultivation. It is necessary to keep a deep and shallow tube well in front of the pond so that it is necessary for quick water for emergency needs.</li><li>
       In the rainy season or excess rain so that the pond does not break, it is necessary to repair the necessary repair beforehand.
       Above all, the pond should be selected in areas where communication facilities are good and have adequate security measures.</li></ul>
		</p>
